{"title_page": "Casey Cott", "text_new": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|American actor}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2017}} \n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Casey Cott\n| image              = Casey Cott by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| alt                = Photo of a bespectacled man with a microphone\n| caption            = Cott at the 2018 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_name         = Casey Morton Cott\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1992|8|8}}\n| birth_place        = \n| residence          = [[New York City]], United States\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|singer}}\n| years_active       = 2011\u2013present\n| relatives          = [[Corey Cott]] (brother)\n| education          = [[Boston University]]<br>[[Carnegie Mellon University]] ([[Bachelor of Fine Arts|BFA]])\n}}\n'''Casey Morton Cott'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/article/cue-a-gigi-star-corey-cott-on-pokemon-borrowing-shoes-for-a-callback-and-the-dog-actor-renaissance-com-346054|title=CUE & A: Gigi Star Corey Cott on Pokemon, Borrowing Shoes for a Callback and The 'Dog Actor Renaissance'|last=Blank|first=Matthew|date=April 7, 2015|website=Playbill|access-date=November 22, 2018}}</ref> (born August 8, 1992)<ref>{{cite twitter |user=CaseyCott|author=Casey Cott|number=895104515183005696|date=August 8, 2017|title=Thank you for the kind birthday wishes! I have never been tagged in so many photos with @ShawnMendes. Happy birthday to you as well man!}}</ref><ref name=\"Out\"/> is an American actor, known for his role as [[Kevin Keller (comics)|Kevin Keller]] on [[The CW]] series ''[[Riverdale (2017 TV series)|Riverdale]]''.\n\n==Early life and education==\nCott was born in 1992, the middle of three children of Rick Cott, an investment manager and former fighter pilot in the Air Force, and Lori Cott (n\u00e9e Morton).<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://senestudio.com/blogs/live/cott-fam|title=This Family Is Taking Over Broadway, TV and Finance|work=Sene|access-date=2018-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724032119/https://senestudio.com/blogs/live/cott-fam|archive-date=July 24, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> Cott grew up in [[Chagrin Falls, Ohio]] with his younger sister and older brother, actor [[Corey Cott]], and graduated from [[Chagrin Falls High School]].<ref name=\"PostGazette\">{{cite web|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/ae/theater-dance/2014/08/29/Newsies-star-Corey-Cott-returns/stories/201408290207|title='Newsies' star Corey Cott returns to Pittsburgh to cheer on brother|work=[[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]]|accessdate=2017-05-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nowcasting.com/actor/popup/viewactor.php?actorID=cmc|title=Now Casting - Casey Cott Resume|website=www.nowcasting.com|access-date=2018-07-23}}</ref> He attended [[Boston University]] for two years before deciding to study acting, transferring to the [[Carnegie Mellon School of Drama]], where he graduated in 2016.<ref name=\"CottBioCWTVPR\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.cwtvpr.com/the-cw/shows/riverdale/bios?id=casey-cott|title=The CW Press \u2013 Riverdale|website=www.cwtvpr.com|accessdate=2017-05-11}}</ref><ref name=\"PostGazette\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cmu.edu/news/stories/archives/2017/may/tony-nominees.html|title=Carnegie Mellon Drama Alumni Nominated for 2017 Tony Awards|work=Carnegie Mellon University|date=May 2, 2017|access-date=2017-09-09}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nCott began his acting career performing in local Ohio theater, appearing in productions of ''[[Bloody Bloody Andrew Jackson]]'' and ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'', among others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abouttheartists.com/artists/479689-casey-cott|title=Casey Cott Theatre Credits and Profile|website=www.abouttheartists.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nowcasting.com/actor/popup/viewactor.php?actorID=cmc|title=Now Casting - Casey Cott Resume|website=www.nowcasting.com|access-date=2018-07-23}}</ref> Upon moving to Pittsburgh for school, he got involved in the area's regional theater scene while performing in university theater productions concurrently.<ref name=\"PostGazette\" /> He appeared in a 2014 production of the play ''Parade'' at the New Hazlett Theater in [[Pittsburgh]], where he starred alongside several of his Carnegie Mellon classmates, as well as a production of ''[[Small Engine Repair]]'' at [[Barebones productions|Barebone Productions]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://drama.cmu.edu/people/alumni/casey-cott/|title=Casey Cott - Carnegie Mellon University School of Drama|work=Carnegie Mellon University School of Drama|access-date=2018-07-23|language=en-US}}</ref> In August 2016, he played Moses in the premiere concert reading of [[Stephen Schwartz (composer)|Stephen Schwartz]]'s musical project, a [[The Prince of Egypt (musical)|stage production]] of ''[[The Prince of Egypt]]'', at the Bay Street Theater in [[Sag Harbor, New York]], opposite [[Shuler Hensley]] and [[John Cariani]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/article/completed-prince-of-egypt-to-receive-starry-concert-reading|title=Completed Prince of Egypt to Receive Starry Concert Reading|website=Playbill|accessdate=2017-05-11}}</ref>\n\nOn March 12, 2016, during his final year at CMU, Cott was cast as [[Kevin Keller (comics)|Kevin Keller]] on the CW drama series ''[[Riverdale (2017 TV series)|Riverdale]]'', a TV adaptation of the [[Archie Comics]] universe. The character of Kevin is notable due to his status of being the first [[openly gay]] character in the history of Archie Comics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2016/03/12/riverdale-cw-archie-pilot-cast-kevin-keller-gay-teen-casey-cott/|title=The CW's ''Riverdale'' Pilot Casts Newbie as Gay Student Kevin Keller|work=[[TVLine]]|last=Slezak|first=Michael|date=March 12, 2016|accessdate=2016-03-14}}</ref> Cott stated in a [[Facebook]] video released to fans in March 2017 that he originally auditioned for the roles of [[Archie Andrews]] and [[Jughead Jones]], prior to landing the role of Kevin.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://toofab.com/2017/03/09/riverdale-star-casey-cott-auditioned-for-archie-7-takeaways-from-his-facebook-live-chat/|title='Riverdale' Star Casey Cott Auditioned for Archie - 7 Takeaways From His Facebook Live|website=Toofab}}</ref> He was promoted to a series regular for the second season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://screenrant.com/riverdale-season-2-casey-cott-kevin-series-regular/|title=Riverdale: Kevin Keller Actor Promoted to Series Regular|date=May 12, 2017|work=Screen Rant|accessdate=2017-05-13}}</ref>\n\nOn March 12, 2018, at the [[South by Southwest|SXSW]] Festival, Cott announced his upcoming role in the film ''The Mascot'', written and directed by Matthew Perkins. Cott will be playing the lead role of Nick Shepherd, an ex-quarterback turned mascot. However, as of early 2019, production has stalled on the project.<ref>{{Citation|title=The Mascot|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt8139924/|access-date=2019-03-07}}</ref> In the second half of 2018, Cott took part in the filming of the movie ''All the Little Things We Kill'', in which he plays the supporting role of Trever Olsson.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/04/elizabeth-marvel-all-the-little-things-we-kill-bryce-durfee-foreign-exchange-1202378525/|title=Elizabeth Marvel To Star In \u2018All The Little Things We Kill\u2019; Bryce Durfee Joins \u2018Foreign Exchange\u2019|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|last2=N'Duka|first2=Amanda|date=2018-04-30|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-03-07}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, it was announced that Cott will star as the titular character in a [[John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts|Kennedy Center]] production of ''[[The Who's Tommy]]'', starring opposite [[Mandy Gonzalez]] and [[Christian Borle]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadway.com/buzz/195059/casey-cott-mandy-gonzalez-christian-borle-more-to-star-in-tommy-at-the-kennedy-center/|title=Casey Cott, Mandy Gonzalez, Christian Borle & More to Star in Tommy at the Kennedy Center|website=Broadway.com|language=en|access-date=2019-03-07}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n{{Expand section|date=November 2018}}\nCott resides in [[New York City]].<ref name=\"CottBioCWTVPR\" />\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''All the Little Things We Kill''\n| Trevor Olsson\n| Completed\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|-\n| 2017\u2013present\n| ''[[Riverdale (2017 TV series)|Riverdale]]''\n| [[Kevin Keller (comics)|Kevin Keller]]\n| Recurring role (season 1); main role (season 2\u2013present)\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]''\n| Lucas Hale\n| Episode: \"Conversion\" \n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Instinct (2018 TV series)|Instinct]]''\n| Dino Moretti\n| Episode: \"Pilot\"\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Katy Keene (TV series)|Katy Keene]]''\n| Kevin Keller\n| Episode: \"Chapter Ten: Gloria\"<ref>http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20200409cw09/</ref>\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Artist\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2017\n| \"[[Why (Sabrina Carpenter song)|Why]]\"\n| [[Sabrina Carpenter]]\n| <ref>{{cite news|last1=Wass|first1=Mike|title=Sabrina Carpenter \"Why\" Video Is Suitably Whimsical|url=http://www.idolator.com/7666537/sabrina-carpenter-why-video-casey-cott|accessdate=2017-07-21|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=July 20, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"Out\">{{cite news |last1=Collette |first1=Matt |title=Cover Exclusive: Casey Cott Is More Than Your Gay Best Friend |url=https://www.out.com/out-exclusives/2018/8/15/cover-exclusive-casey-cott-more-your-gay-best-friend |work=Out |date=August 15, 2018 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cott, Casey}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Ca